# Config for SwiftFormat by Nick Lockwood (`brew install swiftformat`).
# Apple's `swift-format` reads `.swift-format` (JSON); this file is for the
# more widely-used third-party tool. Run `swiftformat .` from the repo root.
#
# Conservative settings — match what the existing code already does. We're
# not trying to mass-reformat the tree right now; the goal is to give every
# editor the same rules so future diffs don't carry whitespace noise.

--swiftversion 6.0
--indent 4
--maxwidth 120

# Don't reflow what's already wrapped — the code base has plenty of
# carefully-laid-out signatures and switch statements that auto-wrapping
# would scramble.
--wraparguments preserve
--wrapparameters preserve
--wrapcollections preserve

# Leave headers alone. Some files have multi-line context comments at top
# (CLAUDE.md-style breadcrumbs) that the default header rule would strip.
--header ignore

# `self.` insertion is a style argument we don't need to litigate via the
# formatter — let humans pick.
--self init-only

# Skip generated artefacts and vendored binaries.
--exclude **/build, **/Build, **/DerivedData, **/.build, **/Pods, **/Resources/cloudflared
